Uses of Package
voicesplitting.time

  • Packages that use voicesplitting.time 
    Package Description
    voicesplitting.gui
    Provides all of the classes used in running the GUI version of the VoiceSplitting project.
    voicesplitting.parsing
    Provides classes which can read and write MIDI files.
    voicesplitting.time
    Provides classes which contain basic score information about the MIDI data.
  • Classes in voicesplitting.time used by voicesplitting.gui 
    Class and Description
    TimeTracker
    A TimeTracker is able to interpret MIDI tempo, key, and time signature change events and keep track of the song timing in seconds, instead of just using ticks as MIDI events do.
  • Classes in voicesplitting.time used by voicesplitting.parsing 
    Class and Description
    KeySignature
    A KeySignature stores the key signature of a song.
    Tempo
    A Tempo object tracks the speed of MIDI data.
    TimeSignature
    A TimeSignature represents some MIDI data's metrical structure (time signature).
    TimeTracker
    A TimeTracker is able to interpret MIDI tempo, key, and time signature change events and keep track of the song timing in seconds, instead of just using ticks as MIDI events do.
  • Classes in voicesplitting.time used by voicesplitting.time 
    Class and Description
    KeySignature
    A KeySignature stores the key signature of a song.
    Tempo
    A Tempo object tracks the speed of MIDI data.
    TimeSignature
    A TimeSignature represents some MIDI data's metrical structure (time signature).
    TimeTrackerNode
    A TimeTrackerNode represents the state of a musical score at a given time, and is able to convert between MIDI ticks and seconds.
